SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1587
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR BROWN (26).
6755S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 478.630, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to associate
circuit judges in the twentieth judicial circuit.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 478.630, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 478.630,
3 to read as follows:
1 478.630. 1. There shall be two circuit judges in the
2 twentieth judicial circuit consisting of the counties of
3 Franklin, Gasconade and Osage. These judges shall sit in
4 divisions numbered one and two.
5 2. The circuit judge in division two shall be elected
6 in 1980. The circuit judge in division one shall be elected
7 in 1982.
8 3. There shall be one additional associate circuit
9 judge in Franklin County. This associate circuit judge
10 shall not be included in the statutory formula for
11 authorizing additional associate circuit judges per county
12 as provided under section 478.320. The governor shall
13 appoint such judge, and that judge shall serve until January
14 1, 2029. An associate circuit judge shall be elected in
15 2028.
